# Generated by `fieldwork setup-notify`, or copy to ~/.fieldwork/notify.env and
# fill in the value below manually. chmod 600.
#
# This file is loaded by ~/.fieldwork/scripts/notify.sh at runtime. It is
# explicitly denied to Claude in:
#   - sandbox.filesystem.denyRead          (settings.json)
#   - permissions.deny Read/Edit/Write     (settings.json)
# It is NOT in the systemd unit's EnvironmentFile, so its contents do not
# propagate to Claude's environment.
#
# IMPORTANT: never commit this file. Fieldwork's .gitignore ignores local
# notify.env files, but keep the real file outside repos when possible.

# ----- ntfy.sh (default) -----
# Pick a private random topic name. Anyone who knows the topic can read your
# notifications, so don't put it in any public log or screenshot.
#
# Example: NTFY_TOPIC=fieldwork-a1f4c2b8e5d3
NTFY_TOPIC=

# ----- Telegram (alternate) -----
# Uncomment if you'd rather use Telegram. notify.sh prefers NTFY_TOPIC if both
# are set, so leave NTFY_TOPIC empty when using Telegram.
#
# TG_BOT_TOKEN=
# TG_CHAT=
